         there used to be a fun bug that if you casted rest the dead (i believe it was this spell) on your pet several times in a row it would go rogue.  that was fun :).  they would be indiff to everyone (except for you until you FD'd or zoned).  i had 10 or so released pets in a zone....but that was a long time ago.</P><P>there are still some bugs to release pets...if you practice a skill (beg, taunt, etc...) on a pet right as the owner goes LD you can release it.</P><P>i don't know if they fixed it, but ench NPC's used to be able to have unlimited pets.  so if you find a lower level ench, get your MR low and then make a bunch of lower level pets and keep sending it against the ench and letting them get charmed.  you could give the ench NPC a bunch of pets.</P><P><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/"><BR>Abillister "Monkey" Abu - Inverse Logic</a><BR>(cue sad music) the Scrolling Link has died, you are now stuck with me until Abil gets a new sig<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
